-- Billionaire Burkle Buys 60% Stake in Soho House, Times Reports
-- B y   M a r i a   K o l e s n i k o v a
-- 2012-01-14T11:44:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-14/billionaire-burkle-buys-60-stake-in-soho-house-times-reports.html
Billionaire  Ron Burkle  has acquired
a 60 percent stake in Soho House Group from the owners  Richard Caring  and Nick Jones and will become chairman of the company,
the Times of London  reported .  The private members’ club chain was valued at about 250
million pounds ($382 million), the newspaper reported, without
saying where it got the information. The company’s net debt is
expected to drop to 50 million pounds from 90 million pounds,
while new openings are planned in Mumbai, Istanbul, Toronto and
 Chicago  in the next two years, the Times reported. Jones will
remain the chief executive officer, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Maria Kolesnikova in  London  at 
